category: Gnome Mail
requires: GConf2 python python-dbus python-gconf2 python-gnomekeyring python-gtk2.0
sdesc: "Allows using Gmail as default mail app in GNOME"
ldesc: "Gnome Gmail is software which adds support for Gmail to the 
Linux Gnome Desktop. It allows Gmail to be selected as the default mail 
application for the desktop. Unlike other solutions on the net, Gnome 
Gmail supports 'To:', 'Subject:', 'body', 'CC:', and 'BCC:' fields, and 
also supports 'Send to...' from Nautilus. You can send file attachments 
automatically."
